                              Note #2:
 Although Microsoft does not provide an ADMX template to configure this registry value, a custom .ADM template (                    Disable-IPv6-Components-KB929852.adm
) is provided in the CIS Benchmark Remediation Kit to facilitate its configuration. Be aware though that simply turning off the group policy setting in the .ADM template will not "undo" the change once applied. Instead, the opposite setting must be applied to change the registry value to the opposite state.

                              Note:
 This Group Policy path does not exist by default. An updated Group Policy template (                    WindowsUpdate.admx/adml
) is required - it is included with the Microsoft Windows 10 Release 1607 & Server 2016 Administrative Templates (or newer).
